duck: Golub-Dobrzyń County - Golub-Dobrzyń County (powiat golubsko-dobrzyński) is a unit of territorial administration and local government (powiat) in Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship, north-central Poland.
Gmina Golub-Dobrzyń - Gmina Golub-Dobrzyń is a rural gmina (administrative district) in Golub-Dobrzyń County, Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-central Poland.

wiki.text:
'Golub' comes from a Slavic root that means "pigeon" or "dove". It can refer to:

* Golub (surname)
* Golub-Dobrzyń (), a town in Northern Poland. ** Golub, Golub-Dobrzyń ** Gmina
  Golub-Dobrzyń ** Golub-Dobrzyń County
* the Golub Corporation, owner of Price Chopper, named after Neil Golub
